The paper deals with the problem of query evaluation over dynamic databases, which is a fundamental problem in database systems and data structures. The paper focuses on unions of conjunctive queries (UCQs), which are a well-studied class of queries in database theory. The paper also considers the presence of integrity constraints, which are a common feature in database systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these sub-categories are all relevant to the problem studied in the paper.
